# ==========================================================================
# Cloudflare Pages — URL redirects
#
# This file is intentionally almost empty. Two things that used to live
# here have moved elsewhere because `_redirects` was the wrong place:
#
# 1. SPA fallback (was: `/*  /index.html  200`)
#    Cloudflare Pages has built-in SPA routing — requests that don't match
#    a static asset are automatically served the root index.html so client-
#    side routing takes over. Adding an explicit rule here triggered a
#    false-positive "infinite loop detected" warning in Cloudflare's
#    validator, and the built-in behavior is already correct, so we don't
#    need the rule at all.
#
# 2. www -> apex canonical redirect (was: `https://www.mooseglove.com/*  ...`)
#    Cloudflare's `_redirects` parser does not accept absolute-URL sources
#    (only relative paths), so cross-hostname redirects cannot live here.
#    The redirect is configured via Cloudflare Dashboard:
#      Rules -> Redirect Rules -> www-to-apex-canonical
#    with expression `http.host eq "www.mooseglove.com"` and target
#    `https://mooseglove.com${http.request.uri.path}` at status 301.
#
# Anything that would add a genuine relative-path redirect (e.g. renaming
# a route and keeping old links working) should go below this line.
# ==========================================================================
